WEATHER PHENOMENA
Types explained:

RA → Rain
-RA → light rain
+RA → heavy rain
TSRA → Thunderstorm + Rain
CB → Cumulonimbus (dangerous clouds)

Impacts:

Light rain → minor impact
Heavy rain / TSRA → severe capacity drop
CB clouds → pilots avoid → rerouting & holding

CLOUD CEILING
Important threshold:

> 2000 ft → No impact
2000 ft – 100 ft → 10–15% capacity reduction

Low clouds = pilots cannot see runway → slow approach → spacing increases → holding.


